{"TopicId":182378,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Making Planets in KSP, Where Do I Start?","CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-22T20:22:30Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-22T20:22:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, I want to start making planets and planet packs in ksp, but I don\u0027t really know how to do it. I currently have this (images below), but I would like someone to help me that knows how to do it with kopernicus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022OunADQU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022542\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/OunADQU.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022mePpK3p.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022394\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/mePpK3p.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022TY562Xy.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022263\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/TY562Xy.png\u0022 width=\u0022719\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002268PWUhl.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022305\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/68PWUhl.png\u0022 width=\u0022578\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022EcM3rl8.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022566\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/EcM3rl8.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do I do it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-22T21:11:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anybody knows how to do this, I would really appreciate it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tyko","CreatedById":164179,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-22T22:19:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6152585764\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/129540-a-beginners-guide-to-kopernicus-the-basics/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T02:35:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAny other starting places?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T07:55:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIll make a longer post today, but you can download some sample planets, and then just change values and replace textures/height maps to make your planet. Its how I got started on my Rald planet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T12:57:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok, links?\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nI also want to know how to make a biome map and height map for planets aswell.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Adstri","CreatedById":174024,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T13:58:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\npssst over here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://discord.me/kopernicus\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://discord.me/kopernicus\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwe have a discord server for this sort of thing\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T14:08:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223545844\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182378\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550930318\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174024\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Adstriduum\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, Adstriduum said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\npssst over here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://discord.me/kopernicus\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://discord.me/kopernicus\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwe have a discord server for this sort of thing\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks!\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T14:25:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoved to Add-on Discussion\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T17:46:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223545824\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182378\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550926633\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187334\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Johnster_Space_Program\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Johnster_Space_Program said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nok, links?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also want to know how to make a biome map and height map for planets aswell.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Kopernicus/KopernicusExamples/tree/master/KopernicusExamples\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Kopernicus/KopernicusExamples/tree/master/KopernicusExamples\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA heightmap is just a greyscale image... If you need a tutorial about how to make a black and white image, that\u0027s too much to ask here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA biome maps is just a RGB image, and you use a color tool to get the numbers for the colors (and use those in your biome definitions in the config file).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can download my planet too, and look at what I did:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/146375-wip-rald-planetmoon-addon-basically-a-terraformed-mars/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/146375-wip-rald-planetmoon-addon-basically-a-terraformed-mars/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Johnster_Space_Program","CreatedById":187334,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-23T23:16:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223545954\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022182378\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221550943983\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002291917\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerikBalm\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, KerikBalm said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Kopernicus/KopernicusExamples/tree/master/KopernicusExamples\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Kopernicus/KopernicusExamples/tree/master/KopernicusExamples\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA heightmap is just a greyscale image... If you need a tutorial about how to make a black and white image, that\u0027s too much to ask here.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA biome maps is just a RGB image, and you use a color tool to get the numbers for the colors (and use those in your biome definitions in the config file).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can download my planet too, and look at what I did:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/146375-wip-rald-planetmoon-addon-basically-a-terraformed-mars/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/146375-wip-rald-planetmoon-addon-basically-a-terraformed-mars/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor biome maps, would a rgb color code look like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ls9sR45.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022696\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/ls9sR45.png\u0022 width=\u0022974\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe numbers for the colors (which in this case is yellow) is the Hex (B6FF00), Right? And I would just put that number in a biome like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022float:none;background-color:rgb(248,249,250);color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:monospace, Courier;font-size:13.93px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18.11px;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003EBiome \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022float:none;background-color:rgb(248,249,250);color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:monospace, Courier;font-size:13.93px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18.11px;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003E{ \u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022float:none;background-color:rgb(248,249,250);color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:monospace, Courier;font-size:13.93px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18.11px;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003Ename = Large Crater\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022float:none;background-color:rgb(248,249,250);color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:monospace, Courier;font-size:13.93px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18.11px;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003Evalue = 10\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022float:none;background-color:rgb(248,249,250);color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:monospace, Courier;font-size:13.93px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18.11px;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003Ecolor = B6FF00\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022float:none;background-color:rgb(248,249,250);color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:monospace, Courier;font-size:13.93px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:18.11px;text-align:left;text-decoration:none;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:pre-wrap;word-spacing:0px;\u0022\u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-25T14:21:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHonestly, you should look at my files for Rald, I have a biome map in there, and you can see how I did it in the configs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts much easier to look at examples than to try and explain it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}